  <h3>Spacing between text styles</h3>

  <p>Use spacers between text styles to establish hierarchy and maintain relationships. For example, if text styles are spaced too closely, the content in the group will be hard to process. If they’re spaced too far apart, it won’t appear as if the styles are related to each other.</p>

  <img src="{{ '/assets/spacing/spacing-typography-2.svg' | url }}" alt="Spacing between text styles" style="">

  <h3>Titles and headlines</h3>

  <p>The spacing between <em>Layout titles and headlines</em> as well as <em>Card titles and body copy</em> is <strong>always</strong> the same at 16px on desktop, tablet, and mobile. It’s enough space so that the title can introduce the content underneath. For visual examples, <a href="https://xd.adobe.com/view/6fdecb88-71b6-447f-8069-9838b6d3668a-3a8d/">see this XD document</a>.</p>

